title: DE-1 Retarding Ion Mass Spectrometer 1-min temperature and density data (low channel used for H+, He++, high channel for He+, O+, O++) - Dr. Charles R. Chappell (NASA/MSFC)

info.x_cadence_note: Cadence based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/de/de1/plasma_rims/plasma_1min_cdf/1981/de1_1min_rims_19811007_v01.cdf. This most common cadence occurred for 37.2588% of the 4132 timesteps. Cadence = 56000 [ms] = PT56S.
